(44, 7, 26, 1, 45, 24, 24, 'ye are brethren; why do ye wrong', 'Conflict Resolution Among Brethren', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of unity among brethren and discourage conflict. In Acts, the plea is made to avoid wrongdoing to one another, while in Genesis, the instruction is to not fall out by the way.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
