(44, 7, 32, 2, 3, 15, 15, 'the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob', 'God of Abraham, Isaac, Jacob', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of God as ''the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.'' This connection highlights the continuity of God''s relationship with the patriarchs and His ongoing covenant with their descendants.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 7, 32, 11, 19, 13, 13, NULL, 'Divine Encounter and Reverence', 'This connection highlights the theme of encountering God, where both Moses and Elijah respond with fear and reverence. In Acts, Moses trembles before God''s declaration, while Elijah covers his face upon hearing God''s voice.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
